Blue Zones – Ladder of Life phase

Many people want their products to be available for “asamiya”, youngest generation of Iranian ladies and gentleman.

Eliran Shtiwi – NELIOI

“The highest decision on a product’s quality and result, and on brand name sits up in the Iran’s youths, but I believe that they don’t care much about targeting health benefits, but rather too much into the differences in their appearance.”

Cities as a target – Ladder of Life phase

“Local and international investors will most probably invest more in creating larger distribution channels and control old financial system, which will eventually help youth to get access to better products at lower cost. Then, and only then, products with health benefits, which will not improve health but instead improve appearance, youth will buy them. “

Of course, this thinking is logical – if a product doesn’t have a real health benefit and all it does is basically “consumerslaves” them, it will never get more than minimum selling and has no chance to expand in Iran’s growing markets. In the event none of the blue zones above can be used effectively in growing sales there are two more channels open and in place already.
